6. Planned changes to improve safety.



The Peru Facility has an on-going commitment to improve safety and protect the environment. In addition to scheduled internal company audits and inspections, the Peru Facility performs an annual self-evaluation as a Star Site in OSHA's Voluntary Protection Program. The following health, safety and environmental improvements are anticipated during the next five years:

- Improvements to the facility's barge dock and styrene unloading system, including structural improvements and enhancements to emergency response capabilities;

- The installation of cyclones on packout bins for better particulate collection;

- Improvements with regard to reactor overfill protection;

- An enhanced Facility Siting Plan as a result of a comprehensive updated Facility Siting Study; 

- The enhancement of Emergency Siren Coverage throughout the plant; and

- Improvements related to Arcflash overduty protection.
